From e873af365b833b031a85286462fadc47ba7bdfad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: raghugr2013-lgtm <raghu@coinnike.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 04:14:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(prod-compose): propagate ENABLE_* feature flags into
 factory-backend
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause
----------
docker-compose `--env-file` supplies variables only for YAML
interpolation. To reach the container's os.environ they must be
enumerated under the service's `environment:` block. The
factory-backend service in infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml
was missing ENABLE_LEGACY_ROUTERS, ENABLE_FACTORY_RUNNER and
ENABLE_DYNAMIC_MARKET_UNIVERSE, so backend/app/core/config.py's
_bool_env(default=False) returned False regardless of what the
production .env said.

Observable symptom (v1.1.0 deploy, commit 546d0a9)
--------------------------------------------------
  legacy routers dormant (ENABLE_LEGACY_ROUTERS=false)
  OpenAPI advertised only 19 paths (Phase-1 core)
  /api/governance/*, /api/deployment/registry, /api/dashboard/* → 404
  Dashboard Governance + Universe widgets empty

Fix
---
Enumerate the three ENABLE_* flags under
services.factory-backend.environment with the same defaults as the
dev overlay compose (docker-compose.yml lines 83-85) and the
factory-runner service in this same file (lines 176-177). No other
change; only the 15-key allow-list grows to 18.

Verification (run on the VPS after redeploy)
--------------------------------------------
  docker exec factory-backend printenv ENABLE_LEGACY_ROUTERS  # → true
  docker logs factory-backend | grep 'legacy full-recovery mount'
  docker exec factory-backend curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8001/api/openapi.json \
    | python3 -c 'import sys,json;print(len(json.load(sys.stdin)["paths"]))'
  # → 600+ (was 19)
  curl -fsS https://strategy.coinnike.com/api/governance/survivor-registry \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"  # → 200

Drift analysis
--------------
Full comparison of factory-backend.environment between dev overlay
and prod compose shows these are the ONLY missing backend runtime
env vars. All other differences are intentional (prod removes
default fallbacks for MONGO_URL / JWT_SECRET / ADMIN_EMAIL /
ADMIN_PASSWORD so boot fails fast on unset required values). No
other feature flag is silently disabled by this class of drift.

Refs
----
Closes deployment-config drift reported after strategy.coinnike.com
v1.1.0 deploy. No route restoration required; existing legacy
routers mount correctly once the flag actually reaches os.environ.
---
 infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml b/infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml
index 245c8b3..614e910 100644
--- a/infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml
+++ b/infra/compose/docker-compose.prod.yml
@@ -52,6 +52,18 @@ services:
       BUILD_VERSION: ${BUILD_VERSION:-1.0.0}
       BUILD_COMMIT: ${BUILD_COMMIT:-unknown}
       BUILD_DATE: ${BUILD_DATE:-unknown}
+      # ── Feature flags ────────────────────────────────────────────
+      # Must be enumerated here (not just present in `.env`) because
+      # docker-compose `--env-file` only supplies interpolation values
+      # — variables absent from this `environment:` block never enter
+      # the container's os.environ. Backend reads these via
+      # backend/app/core/config.py:_bool_env (default False), so an
+      # omitted flag silently disables the feature at boot. Kept in
+      # sync with dev overlay (docker-compose.yml, lines 83-85) and
+      # the factory-runner service in this file (lines 176-177).
+      ENABLE_LEGACY_ROUTERS: ${ENABLE_LEGACY_ROUTERS:-true}
+      ENABLE_FACTORY_RUNNER: ${ENABLE_FACTORY_RUNNER:-true}
+      ENABLE_DYNAMIC_MARKET_UNIVERSE: ${ENABLE_DYNAMIC_MARKET_UNIVERSE:-false}
     networks:
       vqb-network:
         aliases:
-- 
